    {
        "content": "<p>Which formulation is better:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Consider the family <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mspace></mspace><mspace width=\"0.1111111111111111em\"/><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0.17em\"></mo><mtext> ⁣</mtext><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">:</mo><mspace width=\"0.3333333333333333em\"/><mi>F</mi><mi>P</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>G</mi><mi>P</mi><msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mi>P</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\{k_P\\colon FP\\to GP\\}_P</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.03148em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace nobreak\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1111111111111111em;\"></span><span class=\"mpunct\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mrel\">:</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.3333333333333333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">FP</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">GP</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> of morphisms.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Consider the family of morphisms <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mspace></mspace><mspace width=\"0.1111111111111111em\"/><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0.17em\"></mo><mtext> ⁣</mtext><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">:</mo><mspace width=\"0.3333333333333333em\"/><mi>F</mi><mi>P</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>G</mi><mi>P</mi><msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mi>P</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\{k_P\\colon FP\\to GP\\}_P</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.03148em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace nobreak\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1111111111111111em;\"></span><span class=\"mpunct\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mrel\">:</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.3333333333333333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">FP</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">GP</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>",
        "id": 258404114,
        "sender_full_name": "Leopold Schlicht",
        "timestamp": 1634749236
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In your example, there's not much difference between the two. But often (1) is preferable. E.g. in the sentence \"Consider a category <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68611em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">C</span></span></span></span> with a distinguished object <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>.\", it's awkward to rewrite to place <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbf C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68611em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">C</span></span></span></span> at the end. You could say something like \"Consider a category with a distinguished object <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">C</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold\">C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(\\mathbf C, X \\in \\mathbf C)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">C</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbf\">C</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>.\", though this doesn't read as nicely for me.</p>",
        "id": 258404790,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathanael Arkor",
        "timestamp": 1634749468
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think the second is better, because it avoids splitting up 'family of morphisms'. If I read the first, I might read 'family' and then the set and think 'family of what?', until reading the end of the sentence</p>",
        "id": 258405959,
        "sender_full_name": "Nick Hu",
        "timestamp": 1634749905
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am not a native speaker, but 2 sounds better to me in this case. I believe 1 is better in cases where you specify what kind of morphisms you are talking about, i.e.: consider the family <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>:</mo><mi>F</mi><mi>P</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>G</mi><mi>P</mi><msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mi>P</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\{k_P : FP \\to GP\\}_P</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.03148em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">FP</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">GP</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> of morphisms that (e.g.) are in the image of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>U</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">U</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span></span></span></span>. However, 2 can also be better if you want to add precisions to the family, i.e.: consider the family of morphisms <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>:</mo><mi>F</mi><mi>P</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>G</mi><mi>P</mi><msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mi>P</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\{k_P:FP \\to GP\\}_P</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.03148em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">FP</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">GP</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> that (e.g.) is of cardinality <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>κ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\kappa</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">κ</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 258405978,
        "sender_full_name": "Ralph Sarkis",
        "timestamp": 1634749913
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am a native speaker but 2 sounds better to me.    But these issues are a bit subtle; for example I also agree with Nathaniel that</p>\n<p>\"Consider a category C with a distinguished object X\"</p>\n<p>sounds infinitely better than</p>\n<p>\"Consider a category with distinguished object X, C.\"</p>\n<p>or even the less terrible alternative he mentioned.</p>",
        "id": 258750274,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1634926049
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't think \"consider a category C with a distinguished object X\" is an instance of 2.  Here \"a category\" is a sufficient description of what C is, and then afterwards we <em>also</em> consider a distinguished object X of C.  By contrast, in the OP question, \"the family\" is not a sufficient description of what <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mspace></mspace><mspace width=\"0.1111111111111111em\"/><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0.17em\"></mo><mtext> ⁣</mtext><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">:</mo><mspace width=\"0.3333333333333333em\"/><mi>F</mi><mi>P</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>G</mi><mi>P</mi><msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mi>P</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\{k_P\\colon FP\\to GP\\}_P</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.03148em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace nobreak\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1111111111111111em;\"></span><span class=\"mpunct\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mrel\">:</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.3333333333333333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">FP</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">GP</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is; what it is (all on its own) is \"a family of morphisms\".</p>",
        "id": 258750568,
        "sender_full_name": "Mike Shulman",
        "timestamp": 1634926200
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, it's too complicated for me: \"category with distinguished object\" is a reasonable kind of thing to consider, like \"pointed set\", but \"category with distinguished object X\" is not a reasonable kind of thing to consider: you never wake up and say \"I want to prove a theorem about a category with a distinguished object called X\".</p>",
        "id": 258751126,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1634926465
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I just know how to write fairly well; I can't really explain the theory of how to do it.</p>",
        "id": 258751332,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1634926557
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i think about this exact problem quite a lot, and, to give a different answer from the consensus here, these days i opt to write something like “consider the family <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><msub><mi>k</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mi>P</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\{k_P\\}_P</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.03148em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> of morphisms <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mi>P</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>G</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">FP\\to GP</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">FP</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">GP</span></span></span></span>”</p>",
        "id": 258826765,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Hosgood",
        "timestamp": 1634999837
